b'' b'text b'' b'trai-gunya-visaya veda' b'nistrai-gunyo bhavarjuna' b'nirdvandvo nitya-sattva-stho' b'niryoga-ksema atmavan' b'' b'trai-gunya--pertaining to the three modes of material nature;' b'visayah--on the subject matter; vedah--vedic literatures;' b'nistrai-gunyah--transcendental to the three modes of material nature;' b'bhava--be; arjuna--o arjuna; nirdvandvah--without duality;' b'nitya-sattva-sthah--in a pure state of spiritual existence;' b'niryoga-ksemah--free from ideas of gain and protection;' b'atma-van--established in the self.' b'' b'translation' b'' b'the vedas deal mainly with the subject of the three modes of material' b'nature. o arjuna, become transcendental to these three modes. be free' b'from all dualities and from all anxieties for gain and safety, and be' b'established in the self.' b'' b'purport' b'' b'all material activities involve actions and reactions in the three' b'modes of material nature. they are meant for fruitive results, which' b'cause bondage in the material world. the vedas deal mostly with fruitive' b'activities to gradually elevate the general public from the field of' b'sense gratification to a position on the transcendental plane. arjuna,' b'as a student and friend of lord krsna, is advised to raise himself to' b'the transcendental position of vedanta philosophy where, in the' b'beginning, there is brahma-jijnasa, or questions on the supreme' b'transcendence. all the living entities who are in the material world are' b'struggling very hard for existence. for them the lord, after creation of' b'the material world, gave the vedic wisdom advising how to live and get' b'rid of the material entanglement. when the activities for sense' b'gratification, namely the karma-kanda chapter, are finished, then the' b'chance for spiritual realization is offered in the form of the' b'upanisads, which are part of different vedas, as the bhagavad-gita is a' b'part of the fifth veda, namely the mahabharata. the upanisads mark the' b'beginning of transcendental life.' b'' b'as long as the material body exists, there are actions and reactions in' b'the material modes. one has to learn tolerance in the face of dualities' b'such as happiness and distress, or cold and warmth, and by tolerating' b'such dualities become free from anxieties regarding gain and loss. this' b'transcendental position is achieved in full krsna consciousness when one' b'is fully dependent on the good will of krsna.' b'' b'bhagavad-gita as it is' b'books of a.c. bhaktivedanta swami' b'' b'' b'---------------------------------------------------------' b"| don't forget to chant: b'| b'| hare krishna hare krishna, krishna krishna hare hare b'| hare rama hare rama, rama rama hare hare b'| b"| kalki's infoline bbs aiken, south carolina, usa b'---------------------------------------------------------' 